# @decision DEC-CI-SEEDS-LINT-LF-001
# @title seeds package — enforce LF line endings on source files
# @status accepted
# @rationale Biome (the project linter) enforces LF line endings. On Windows,
#   git core.autocrlf=true checks files out as CRLF, causing 64 biome violations
#   on every CI run that misses the turbo seeds-lint cache (e.g., when upstream
#   packages like @yakcc/shave are touched and the cache is invalidated). These
#   .gitattributes rules override core.autocrlf for seeds source files, ensuring
#   git stores AND checks out LF regardless of local OS settings. Without this
#   pin, any Windows contributor re-introduces the CRLF drift on their next
#   commit. This is the canonical fix: biome --write normalizes the working copy,
#   .gitattributes keeps it normalized forever.
#
# Affects: packages/seeds/src/**/*.ts, packages/seeds/src/**/*.json

*.ts   text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
